  "prompt": "What are the best free WordPress plugins in 2014?",
  "response": "In 2014, several free WordPress plugins were highly regarded for their functionality and ease of use. While the plugin landscape has evolved since then, here are some of the best free WordPress plugins that were popular in 2014:\n\n### 1. **Yoast SEO**\n   - **Purpose**: SEO optimization.\n   - **Features**: Helps improve your site's SEO with tools like meta descriptions, XML sitemaps, and keyword analysis.\n\n### 2. **Akismet**\n   - **Purpose**: Spam protection.\n   - **Features**: Automatically filters out spam comments, keeping your site clean.\n\n### 3. **Wordfence Security**\n   - **Purpose**: Security.\n   - **Features**: Includes a firewall, malware scanner, and login security to protect your site from threats.\n\n### 4. **Contact Form 7**\n   - **Purpose**: Contact forms.\n   - **Features**: Allows you to create and manage multiple contact forms with ease.\n\n### 5. **W3 Total Cache**\n   - **Purpose**: Performance optimization.\n   - **Features**: Improves site speed and user experience by caching pages, reducing load times.\n\n### 6. **Jetpack by WordPress.com**\n   - **Purpose**: Multifunctional tool.\n   - **Features**: Offers a suite of features including site stats, related posts, social sharing, and more.\n\n### 7. **WP Super Cache**\n   - **Purpose**: Caching.\n   - **Features**: Generates static HTML files from your dynamic WordPress blog, speeding up load times.\n\n### 8. **Google XML Sitemaps**\n   - **Purpose**: SEO.\n   - **Features**: Creates an XML sitemap for your site, helping search engines like Google index it more efficiently.\n\n### 9. **UpdraftPlus**\n   - **Purpose**: Backup.\n   - **Features**: Automatically backs up your site and allows you to restore it with a single click.\n\n### 10. **Broken Link Checker**\n   - **Purpose**: Link management.\n   - **Features**: Monitors your site for broken links and missing images, helping maintain site integrity.\n\n### 11. **WP-Optimize**\n   - **Purpose**: Database optimization.\n   - **Features**: Cleans and optimizes your WordPress database to improve performance.\n\n### 12. **Social Sharing Toolkit**\n   - **Purpose**: Social media integration.\n   - **Features**: Adds social sharing buttons to your posts and pages, making it easy for visitors to share your content.\n\n### 13. **iThemes Security (formerly Better WP Security)**\n   - **Purpose**: Security.\n   - **Features**: Protects your site from common threats by hiding vulnerabilities and strengthening user credentials.\n\n### 14. **NextGEN Gallery**\n   - **Purpose**: Image galleries.\n   - **Features**: Allows you to create and manage beautiful image galleries on your site.\n\n### 15. **All in One SEO Pack**\n   - **Purpose**: SEO optimization.\n   - **Features**: Another comprehensive SEO plugin that helps improve your site's search engine rankings.\n\nThese plugins were essential tools for WordPress users in 2014, offering a range of functionalities from SEO and security to performance optimization and social media integration. While some of these plugins have evolved or been surpassed by newer options, many of them remain relevant and widely used today.",
